A '''Holy See Representative''' is a papal diplomat (representing the [[Holy See]] and [[Vatican City State]]), usually ranking as [[papal nuncio]] (equivalent to ambassador), who is accredited to an international organisation, where (other) nations dispatch [[Permanent representative]]s.
==Worldwide organisations== As of January 2016, there were 22 representatives, accredited to the following host organisations : * [[Food and Agricultural Organization of the United Nations]] (FAO) Msgr.[[Fernando Chica Arellano]] * [[International Atomic Energy Agency]] (IAEA) Msgr. [[Janusz Urbańczyk]] * [[International Committee of Military Medicine]] (ICMM) Msgr. [[Robrecht Boone]] * [[International Institute for the Unification of Private Law]] (UNIDROIT) Dr. [[Giuseppe Dalla Torre]] Del Tempio di Sanguinetto * [[International Organization for Migration]] (IOM) Archbishop [[Ivan Jurkovič]] * [[Organisation for the Prohibition of Chemical Weapons]] (OPCW) Archbishop [[Aldo Cavalli]] * [[Preparatory Commission for the Comprehensive Nuclear-Test-Ban Treaty Organization]] (CTBTO) Msgr. [[Janusz Urbańczyk]] * [[United Nations Educational, Scientific and Cultural Organization]] (UNESCO) Msgr. [[Francesco Follo]] * [[United Nations Human Settlements Programme]] (UN-Habitat) Archbishop [[Charles Daniel Balvo]] * [[United Nations Industrial Development Organization]] (UNIDO) Msgr. Janusz Urbańczyk * [[Permanent Observer of the Holy See to the United Nations|United Nations headquarters]] (UN), New York, NY (USA) – Archbishop [[Bernardito Auza]] ** [[Permanent Observer of the Holy See to the United Nations in Geneva|Office of the United Nations and Specialized Institutions in Geneva]] (UNOG) Archbishop Ivan Jurkovič ** [[United Nations Office at Vienna|Office of the United Nations and Specialized Institutions in Vienna]] (UNOV) Msgr. Janusz Urbańczyk * [[World Tourism Organization]] (WTO) Msgr. [[Maurizio Bravi]] * [[World Trade Organization]] (WTO) Archbishop Ivan Jurkovič
==Regional== * [[African Union]] (AU) Archbishop [[Luigi Bianco]] * [[Association of Southeast Asian Nations]] (ASEAN) Archbishop [[Leopoldo Girelli]] * [[Council of Europe]] Msgr. [[Paolo Rudelli]] * [[Economic Community of West African States]] (ECOWAS) vacant * [[League of Arab States]] (LAS) Archbishop [[Bruno Musarò]] * [[Organization for Security and Co-operation in Europe]] (OSCE) Msgr. Janusz Urbańczyk * [[Organization of American States]] (OAS) Archbishop Bernardito Auza
