'''Iraqi Communist Vanguard Organisation''' was a political organization in [[Iraq]]. The organisation was set up by the [[Ba'ath Party|Baath]]ist regime after the break between the Baath Party and the [[Iraqi Communist Party]] in 1979. The Iraqi Communist Vanguard Organisation was used by the regime to issue criticism against the Communist Party, claiming that the Communist Party had 'given up the struggle'.<ref>Ismael, Tareq Y. ''[https://books.google.com/books?id=6uAvs4HqVLIC The Rise and Fall of the Communist Party of Iraq]''. [[Cambridge]]/[[New York City|New York]]: Cambridge University Press, 2008. pp. 185-186</ref>

